        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(edit): unwrap XML-RPC {item: {oldText, newText}} edit entries",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nAdds XML-RPC-style `{ item: ... }` edit-entry unwrapping in edit argument\npreparation and direct execution. XML-RPC array-of-structs wraps each element\nas `{item: {oldText, newText}}` instead of the canonical flat entry format.\nFixes #75152.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run src/agents/sessions/tools/edit.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  12 passed (12) — including both wrapper tests\n```\n\n### Test fix\n\nTest data now actually exercises the wrapper format:\n- `edits: [{ item: { oldText, newText } }]` for single wrapped entry\n- `edits: [{ oldText, newText }, { item: { oldText, newText } }]` for mixed\n\nPreviously the tests used canonical entries that would pass even without\nthe unwrap logic.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
